		<h2 id="DSArtifact">Data Service Artifact</h2>
        <p>
        To create a data service, right click on the CApp project and select <strong>Data Service</strong> from the 
        menu. 
        </p>
		<p>
			<br></br>
			<br></br>
			<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/ds1.png"></img>
			<br></br>
			<br></br>
		</p>
		<p>
		There are three ways to create a data service.    
		</p>
		<ol>
			<li>New Data Service</li>
			<li>Import Data Service from File System</li>
			<li>Import Data Service from Registry</li>
		</ol>
		<p>
			<br></br>
			<br></br>
			<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/ds2.png"></img>
			<br></br>
			<br></br>
		</p>

			<p>With the <strong>New Data Service</strong> option, you will get an empty data service with the specified name. At the same time, 
			you can upload a <strong>Data Service</strong> file or any file with the extension of <strong>.dbs</strong> from the 
			file system or from the registry.
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/ds3.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>
			
			<p>With the <strong>Import Data Service from Registry</strong>, you can browse resources of the registry instance that you 
			have already created or you can create a new registry instance as well. After selecting the registry instance, click on 
			<strong>Browse</strong> to browse resources in registry. 
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/ds4.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>	
			
			<p>Select the CApp project you want to create <strong>Data Service</strong> and click <strong>Finish</strong>.
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/ds5.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>	
			
			<p>Now you will see new Data Service artifact is created under the selected CApp project.
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/ds6.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>			
									
